qas.question: What other ethnic groups live throughout all of Tibet?
What does the population of Tibet consist of?

context: Historically, the population of Tibet consisted of primarily <a1_0><b5_0>ethnic Tibetans<b5_0/><a1_0/> and some other ethnic groups. According to tradition the original ancestors of the Tibetan people, as represented by the <a0_0>six red bands in the Tibetan flag<a0_0/>, are: the <b3_0>Se, Mu, Dong, Tong, Dru and Ra<b3_0/>. Other traditional ethnic groups with significant population or with the majority of the ethnic group residing in Tibet (excluding a disputed area with <a2_0>India<a2_0/>) include <b4_0>Bai people, Blang, Bonan, Dongxiang, Han, Hui people, Lhoba, Lisu people, Miao, Mongols, Monguor<b4_0/> (Tu people), Menba (Monpa), Mosuo, Nakhi, Qiang, Nu people, Pumi, Salar, and Yi people.
